                Petia --- Place Equivalence Through (semipositive) Invariant Analysis
		http://service-technology.org/petia



Version 1.3 (25 Juli 2011)
==========================

* New option -n to exclude trivial invariants from consideration.

Version 1.2 (24 Juli 2011)
==========================

* New option -i to print the separating invariants.

* New option -f to use full invariants instead of support.

Version 1.1 (22 Juli 2011)
==========================

* Option -t to determine an equivalence of transitions instead 	of
  places.

* Fixing a bug occurring in conjunction with empty pre- and/or postsets.

Version 1.0 (20 Juli 2011)
==========================

* First version of Petia

* Determines an equivalence class of places of a net, where two 	places
  are equivalent if in any semipositive place invariant 	both occur or
  both do not occur.

* Incorporates lp_solve, a Linear Programming Solver.

Version 0.0-unreleased (8 Juli 2011)
====================================



